      <div class="content block-columns columns-1 bg-transparent text-default text-left align-top">
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            <div class="block-column">
              <h2 class="sidekick spill-right">The Heart of Campus Robotics</h2><p class="spill-right padded-top">The Anna Hiss Gymnasium serves as a hub for robotics research and innovation on campus. Fully renovated as a state-of-the-art facility, it provides flexible laboratories and fabrication spaces where students and faculty can prototype, test and advance robotic systems. The building supports hands-on experimentation, real-world applications and collaborative projects that push the boundaries of what robots can do.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><div class="lined-list"><p class="lead"><strong>55,000 sq ft</strong> total building space</p><p class="lead"><strong>4</strong> modern fabrication facilities</p><p class="lead"><strong>1,200 sq ft</strong> motion capture studio</p><p class="lead"><strong>Simulated Apartment</strong> for service robotics research</p><p class="lead"><strong>Simulated Operating Room</strong> for surgical robotics research</p><p class="lead"><strong>Heavy Robotics Bay</strong> for robots operating in hazardous environments</p></div>
